DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

install_problem_grader(~~&std_problem_grader);
TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;
$showPartialCredit = 0;

# output the text of the problem

$a = random(2,9,1);
$b = random(2,9,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Find the \( x- \) and \( y- \) intercepts of the graph of
\( y=\displaystyle\frac{$a}{x} + $b \). If some solution does not exist, type
\( N \) for both coordinates. 

\( x- \)intercept is ( \{ans_rule(10)\}, \{ans_rule(10)\} )

\( y- \)intercept is ( \{ans_rule(10)\}, \{ans_rule(10)\} )

EOT

$ans1 = -$a/$b;
$ans2 = 0; 
$ans3 = "n"; 
$ans4 = "n";

ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));
ANS(str_cmp($ans3));
ANS(str_cmp($ans4));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
